   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE DEFINITION OF THE SPIRIT 1 Scripture Reading: Gen 1:2; Judg.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>3:10; 6:34; Gen 6:3a; Psa 51:11; Isa 63:10-11; Luke 1:13-17, 30-36; Matt 1:18-20; Mark 1:10, 12; Matt 4:1; Luke 4:1, 18; John 1:32-33; 7:37-39; 1 Cor 15:45b; Rev 21:6; 22:17c OUTLINE In the Old Testament the Spirit is: The Spirit of God in God's creation of the universe Gen 1:2.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Spirit of Jehovah in God's reaching of men and in His care for men Judg.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>3:10; 6:34; Gen 6:3a.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Spirit of holiness in God's making His chosen people holy unto Himself Psa 51:11; Isa 63:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the New Testament the Spirit is: The Holy Spirit: In the conception of John the Baptist to introduce God's becoming a man in His incarnation Luke 1:13-17.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In the conception of Jesus in God's incarnation to be a man in the flesh Luke 1:30-36; Matt 1:18-20.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Spirit: With whom Jesus was anointed and who was in the move of the man Jesus in His ministry to God on the earth Mark 1:10, 12; Matt 4:1; Luke 4:1, 18; John 1:32-33.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>But in the believers to flow out as rivers of living water was not yet before Christ's glorification resurrection John 7:37-39.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Through and in His resurrection Christ as the last Adam became the life-giving Spirit to enter into His believers to flow out as rivers of living water 1 Cor 15:45b; Rev 21:6; 22:17c.</S>
   </TEXT>
